- [ ] **Step 1.8.3: Opt-in enabler (handles pre-existing global fetch mock)**

Codex round 2 issue #1: existing `jest.setup.js` has `global.fetch = jest.fn()`. MSW won't intercept until we replace fetch with a real implementation FOR THE TEST FILE. Enabler must save/restore fetch.

`tests/mocks/enable-msw.ts`:

```ts
import 'whatwg-fetch';
import { server } from './server';

let savedFetch: typeof globalThis.fetch | undefined;

beforeAll(() => {
  // whatwg-fetch already installed real fetch on globalThis at import time;
  // save whatever was there from jest.setup.js so we can restore after.
  savedFetch = (globalThis as any).__originalJestFetch ?? undefined;
  server.listen({ onUnhandledRequest: 'bypass' });
});

afterEach(() => server.resetHandlers());

afterAll(() => {
  server.close();
  if (savedFetch) {
    globalThis.fetch = savedFetch;
  }
});

export { server };
```

Update `jest.setup.js` to expose its fetch mock for restoration:

```js
// In existing jest.setup.js, find:
//   global.fetch = jest.fn();
// Change to:
const _origFetch = jest.fn();
global.fetch = _origFetch;
globalThis.__originalJestFetch = _origFetch;
```

This is the ONE allowed edit to `jest.setup.js`. It's additive — does not change behavior for existing 22 tests.

(`onUnhandledRequest: 'bypass'` — no fail when a test doesn't mock; existing `global.fetch = jest.fn()` mocks are harmless because in MSW-enabled test files, `whatwg-fetch` overrides them with real fetch.)

